## fonts.rpy - Font definitions reference
##
## NOTE: All font definitions have been moved to gui.rpy for editor compatibility.
## Use the Preset Editor's Game Config tab to edit fonts and sizes.
##
## Font files should be placed in the game/ directory or game/fonts/:
##   - CalSans-Regular.ttf (for character names and UI)
##   - Jua-Regular.ttf (for dialogue text)
##   - DejaVuSans.ttf (for glyphs/special characters)
##   - DejaVuSansMono.ttf (for monospace/typewriter text)
##
## Related files: gui.rpy, styles.rpy

################################################################################
## Fonts defined in gui.rpy (editable via Game Config):
################################################################################
##
## Font Files:
##   gui.text_font - Main dialogue text font
##   gui.name_text_font - Character name font
##   gui.interface_text_font - Interface/button font
##   gui.system_font - System notifications font
##   gui.glyph_font - Special characters/icons font
##   gui.mono_font - Monospace/typewriter font
##
## Font Sizes:
##   gui.text_size - Normal dialogue text size
##   gui.name_text_size - Character name size
##   gui.interface_text_size - Interface text size
##   gui.label_text_size - Label text size
##   gui.notify_text_size - Notification text size
##   gui.title_text_size - Title text size
##   gui.prompt_text_size - Input prompt text size
